(3, 'Minister grijpt in om nieuwe vertraging uitrol 5G te voorkomen', 'https://www.telegraaf.nl/images/1200x630/filters:format(jpeg):quality(80)/cdn-kiosk-api.telegraaf.nl/c24a7e0c-3c64-11ee-965d-02c309bc01c1.jpg', 'Door een slepende ruzie met een satellietbedrijf dreigt opnieuw vertraging bij de uitrol van supersnel mobiel internet (5G) in Nederland. Om dat te voorkomen, pakt minister Micky Adriaansens (Economische Zaken) de frequentie van het bedrijf af.', '1', '1', '7', '2023-08-16 18:43:14', '1,2,4,5', 'De Telegraaf - Financieel Overzicht', NULL, 'business', 'https://www.telegraaf.nl/financieel/49939303/minister-grijpt-in-om-nieuwe-vertraging-uitrol-5-g-te-voorkomen?utm_source=RSS&utm_medium=RSS'),
(4, 'Historians and literary scholars tackle the Shakespeare authorship question', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2023/shakespeare-1.jpg', 'The Journal of Scientific Exploration (JSE), an open access journal, has published its summer issue, which is specially devoted to what is known as the Shakespeare authorship question (SAQ).', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 18:38:07', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-historians-literary-scholars-tackle-shakespeare.html'),
(5, 'Microplastic pollution: New device uses wood dust to trap up to 99.9% of microplastics in water', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2023/microplastic-pollution.jpg', 'Could plants be the answer to the looming threat of microplastic pollution? Scientists at UBC\'s BioProducts Institute found that if you add tannins—natural plant compounds that make your mouth pucker if you bite into an unripe fruit—to a layer of wood dust, you can create a filter that traps virtually all microplastic particles present in water.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 18:38:02', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-microplastic-pollution-device-wood-microplastics.html'),
(6, 'Researchers achieve high-speed super-resolution imaging with a large field of view', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2023/researchers-achieve-hi-2.jpg', 'Researchers have developed a fluorescence microscope that uses structured illumination for fast super-resolution imaging over a wide field of view. The new microscope was designed to image multiple living cells simultaneously with a very high resolution to study the effects of various drugs and mixtures of drugs on the body.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 18:36:03', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-high-speed-super-resolution-imaging-large-field.html'),
(7, 'Researchers improve air pollution exposure models using artificial intelligence and mobility data', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2023/improved-air-pollution.jpg', 'Americans in the Northeast paid greater attention to air quality alerts this summer as wildfire smoke thickened skies with an orange-tinted haze. Smoke and other sources of air pollution contain tiny particles, called fine particulate matter (PM 2.5). Smaller than the width of a human hair, PM 2.5 pose health dangers when inhaled, especially to people with pre-existing heart and lung conditions.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 18:33:04', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-air-pollution-exposure-artificial-intelligence.html'),
(8, 'A Conductor Who Wants to Put You ‘Inside the Sound’', 'https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/08/16/multimedia/16PASCAL-02-mwbc/16PASCAL-02-mwbc-moth.jpg', 'Maxime Pascal, a latecomer to classical music, forged an unusual path to the podium that has paid off for him and for audiences.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 18:30:13', '1,2,4,5', 'The New York Times', 'Joshua Barone', 'entertainment', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2023/08/16/arts/music/maxime-pascal-le-balcon.html'),
(9, 'Authorities to Return Items Seized in Kansas Newspaper Raid', 'https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/08/16/multimedia/16kansas-paper-1-lhck/16kansas-paper-1-lhck-moth.jpg', 'The raid of the newspaper, The Marion County Record, has drawn condemnation from First Amendment advocates.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 18:21:31', '1,2,4,5', 'The New York Times', 'Benjamin Mullin and Kevin Draper', 'business', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2023/08/16/business/media/authorities-return-items-kansas-newspaper-raid.html'),
(10, 'Scientists say deepening Arctic snowpack drives greenhouse gas emissions', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2023/scientists-say-deepeni.jpg', 'Human-caused climate change is shortening the snow cover period in the Arctic. But according to new research led by Earth system scientists at the University of California, Irvine, some parts of the Arctic are getting deeper snowpack than normal, and that deep snow is driving the thawing of long-frozen permafrost carbon reserves and leading to increased emissions of greenhouse gases like carbon dioxide and methane.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 18:17:04', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-scientists-deepening-arctic-snowpack-greenhouse.html'),
(11, 'Michelle Obama reveals the breakfast she ate every day ‘for most of her life’', 'https://static.independent.co.uk/2023/08/16/14/GettyImages-1135975319.jpg?width=1200&auto=webp', '‘I was kind of a picky eater,’ says former first lady', '1', '1', '6', '2023-08-16 18:11:06', '1,2,4,5', 'The Independent - Life and Style', 'Olivia Petter', 'entertainment', 'https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/food-and-drink/michelle-obama-diet-breakfast-b2394065.html'),
(12, 'Fed Officials Avoided a Victory Lap at July Meeting', 'https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/08/16/multimedia/16dc-fedminutes-bgcq/16dc-fedminutes-bgcq-moth.jpg', 'Federal Reserve officials raised interest rates at their July 26 meeting, but investors doubt that they will lift them again this year.', '1', '1', '26', '2023-08-16 18:10:23', '1,2,4,5', 'The New York Times', 'Jeanna Smialek', 'business', 'https://www.nytimes.com/2023/08/16/business/economy/federal-reserve-minutes.html'),
(13, 'Surprisingly deadly summer for Lake Tahoe bears: 20 killed, 18 hurt in vehicle collisions', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2022/black-bear.jpg', 'Twenty bears killed and almost 20 more injured—it\'s been a uniquely dangerous summer for Lake Tahoe\'s bear population, with more hit by vehicles from late July to mid-August \"than we\'ve ever had at that time,\" said Ann Bryant of the Bear League.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 18:10:01', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-deadly-summer-lake-tahoe-vehicle.html'),
(14, 'The Gulf of Mexico is record hot. Here\'s what that means for hurricanes, wildlife', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2019/5-hurricane.jpg', 'Neil Lynch started his Saturday morning like any other: He stopped his car at Belleair Beach, griped about the hourly parking fee and set off on a 5-mile walk.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 18:10:01', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-gulf-mexico-hot-hurricanes-wildlife.html'),
