(21, 'Hoe kon liefdesgeluk Sieneke zo snel verdampen? Pijnlijk gerucht doet de ronde!', 'https://www.telegraaf.nl/images/1200x630/filters:format(jpeg):quality(80)/cdn-kiosk-api.telegraaf.nl/7bf1f500-3c5c-11ee-b72f-0257d57b707f.jpg', 'Ze zouden over drie maanden hun tinnen huwelijk vieren. Maar de handtekening die Sienek en haar echtgenoot Jan tien jaar geleden op hun trouwakte zetten, ’sieren’ binnenkort de scheidingspapieren! Een breuk die in de showbizzwereld uit de lucht komt vallen. Waarom heeft het stel, dat altijd zo hecht leek, de handdoek in de ring gegooid?', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 17:44:00', '1,2,4,5', 'De Telegraaf - Entertainment Overzicht', NULL, 'entertainment', 'https://www.telegraaf.nl/entertainment/1506963358/hoe-kon-liefdesgeluk-sieneke-zo-snel-verdampen-pijnlijk-gerucht-doet-de-ronde?utm_source=RSS&utm_medium=RSS'),
(22, 'Scientists develop artificial metabolic pathway that uses electricity to produce ATP', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2023/understanding-the-elec.jpg', 'When nature performs chemical reactions to create energy-rich compounds from simple molecules, it requires energy. So far, it has not been possible to use human-made electricity to drive these biochemical processes.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 17:39:03', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-scientists-artificial-metabolic-pathway-electricity.html'),
(23, 'UK arrests part of wider western moves to disrupt Russian spy networks', 'https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fd1e00ek4ebabms.cloudfront.net%2Fproduction%2F7f7be725-89fe-426d-9bfd-d66f746e91a4.jpg?source=next-home-page&dpr=2&width=580&fit=scale-down', 'Investigation under Official Secrets Act against five Bulgarian nationals ongoing', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 17:38:06', '1,2,4,5', 'Financial Times', NULL, 'business', 'https://www.ft.com/content/62670504-b37f-48e7-b493-3ead28986dd4'),
(24, 'Assessing controls on ocean productivity—from space', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2023/assessing-controls-on.jpg', 'Phytoplankton determine how much life the ocean is able to support and play a role in controlling atmospheric carbon dioxide concentrations, thereby regulating our climate. These tiny marine plants depend on sunlight as well as nutrients to thrive—including elements such as iron or nitrogen that can be brought to the ocean surface by currents and upwelling.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 17:27:08', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-ocean-productivityfrom-space.html'),
(25, 'Study shows how corals and anemones engage in symbiotic relationships with algae and swap nutrients with them', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2023/study-shows-how-corals.jpg', '\"Eat or be eaten\" is not always the way things are in nature. It can be beneficial for different species to team up and pool their capabilities. Cnidarians such as corals and anemones were already committing to this kind of biological joint venture with algae from the dinoflagellate group 250 million years ago.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 17:26:57', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-corals-anemones-engage-symbiotic-relationships.html'),
