(27, '’ArcelorMittal overweegt overname US Steel’', 'https://www.telegraaf.nl/images/1200x630/filters:format(jpeg):quality(80)/cdn-kiosk-api.telegraaf.nl/5091e2fa-3c5a-11ee-a763-0218eaf05005.jpg', 'Staalmaker ArcelorMittal doet een bod op de Amerikaanse concurrent US Steel. De grootste producent van Europa bespreekt een mogelijke overname met zijn investeringsbankiers, aldus bronnen tegen Reuters.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 17:25:42', '1,2,4,5', 'De Telegraaf - Financieel Overzicht', NULL, 'business', 'https://www.telegraaf.nl/financieel/1908677149/arcelor-mittal-overweegt-overname-us-steel?utm_source=RSS&utm_medium=RSS'),
(28, 'Online outrage can benefit brands that take stances on social issues', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2023/online-outrage-can-ben.jpg', 'Nike\'s advertisement featuring Colin Kaepernick sparked a social media firestorm in 2018. Kaepernick, a former San Francisco 49ers quarterback, first made headlines in 2016 when he protested against police brutality by kneeling during the American national anthem.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 17:20:01', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-online-outrage-benefit-brands-stances.html'),
(29, 'Novel enzyme could boost sustainable production of aviation fuel', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2023/novel-enzyme-could-boo.jpg', 'In recent decades, scientists have sought solutions to improve the sustainable production of biofuels from renewable sources. The latest advance in this field was announced at the end of May by Brazilian researchers and could boost the production of sustainable biofuels for aviation and maritime shipping.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 17:18:10', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-enzyme-boost-sustainable-production-aviation.html'),
(30, 'Study shows bacterial viruses \'glue\' RNA to host proteins', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2023/viruses-glue-rna-to-pr.jpg', 'Until now, RNA and proteins were thought to interact only briefly during cellular processes. Researchers at the Max Planck Institute for Terrestrial Microbiology in Marburg, Germany, have discovered that this is not the case. During their developmental cycle, bacterial viruses \"glue\" specific RNAs to host proteins. As the authors describe in their publication in the journal Nature, \"RNAylation\" could open up new avenues for phage therapy or drug development.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 17:18:03', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-bacterial-viruses-rna-host-proteins.html'),
(31, 'NASA\'s lunar trailblazer gets final payload for moon water hunt', 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2023/nasas-lunar-trailblaze.jpg', 'NASA\'s Lunar Trailblazer is nearing completion now that its second and final cutting-edge science instrument has been added to the small spacecraft. Built by the University of Oxford in England and contributed by the UK Space Agency, the Lunar Thermal Mapper (LTM) joins the High-resolution Volatiles and Minerals Moon Mapper (HVM3), which was integrated with the spacecraft late last year. Together, the instruments will enable scientists to determine the abundance, location, and form of the moon\'s water.', '1', '1', '0', '2023-08-16 17:12:04', '1,2,4,5', 'Phys.org - News And Articles On Science And Technology', NULL, 'science', 'https://phys.org/news/2023-08-nasa-lunar-trailblazer-payload-moon.html'),
